description:
Subjects Addressed: (1) “Stand therefore, having your loins girt about with truth, and having on the breastplate of righteousness.” Ephesians 6:14.
(2) The combination of the first two parts of the armor represents the sealing of God’s people. (3:07)
(3) Discover the principal truths that we must dwell upon and preach. (9:00)
(4) Discover the connection between the breastplate of righteousness and the breastplate of judgment that Aaron wore. (15:20)
(5) As we put on the breastplate of righteousness, we must also have the Urim and the Thummim. Discover what they mean. (29:00)
(6) One reason why we need the Urim and Thummim in our breastplate of righteousness is because we are in a warfare. LGBT activists blame Christians for Orlando massacre at the Pulse Gay Club and SDAs blame anti-LGBT Theology for mass shooting. Consider the connection with emperor Nero of Rome. (34:30)
(7) The Great Controversy pages 444 and 445 are being fulfilled as Pope Francis and several prominent Evangelical and Pentecostal leaders met in Rome last Friday to discuss areas of mutual agreement and where they respectfully disagreed. (39:30)
(8) The Great Controversy page 45 instructs us on how we should respond to “Together 2016” when Protestants and Catholics plan to unite. (42:00)
(9) Revelation 13:3,4,11-15 is being fulfilled as Pope Francis stated the following at a meeting with a delegation of the world communion of Reformed Churches which unites about 225 Protestant Churches in 100 countries: “Our meeting here today is one more step along the journey that marks the ecumenical movement. (45:00)
(10) Revelation 13:15-17 is being fulfilled as “Venezuela Goes from Bad to Catastrophe,” due to economic sanctions by the U.S., the image of the beast. (48:40)
(11) Revelation 13:16-17 is being fulfilled as “The middle class is vanishing in Venezuela and in America's cities.” There will only be two classes in the world, “rich and poor.” (52:25)
(12) “The Christian life is a battle and a march. But the victory to be gained is not won by human power. The field of conflict is the domain of the heart. The battle which we have to fight--the greatest battle that was ever fought by man--is the surrender of self to the will of God, the yielding of the heart to the sovereignty of love. The old nature, born of blood and of the will of the flesh, cannot inherit the kingdom of God. The hereditary tendencies, the former habits, must be given up.” {MB 141.2} (56:55)
